1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,000
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,000
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:02,006 --> 00:00:03,006
(Generative AI technology
was used in certain scenes.)

4
00:00:04,366 --> 00:00:05,433
(Episode 66)

5
00:00:31,686 --> 00:00:33,686
Team Manager!

6
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:35,900
Team Manager!

7
00:00:37,966 --> 00:00:38,966
Team Manager!

8
00:00:49,339 --> 00:00:50,486
Team Manager, are you okay?

9
00:00:51,546 --> 00:00:52,900
What do I do?

10
00:00:54,019 --> 00:00:55,479
What's the matter?

11
00:00:56,533 --> 00:00:58,233
I'll call an ambulance. Hang on.

12
00:00:58,373 --> 00:00:59,373
No.

13
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:01,239
I'm fine. Really.

14
00:01:01,660 --> 00:01:02,786
Are you sure you're okay?

15
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:05,840
Of course.

16
00:01:06,660 --> 00:01:07,660
I mean...

17
00:01:07,946 --> 00:01:08,946
I'm sorry. I...

18
00:01:09,766 --> 00:01:10,899
I just got a little carsick.

19
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:13,179
What? Carsick?

20
00:01:19,066 --> 00:01:21,426
You should've driven properly.

21
00:01:21,746 --> 00:01:23,119
This wasn't a roller coaster.

22
00:01:25,939 --> 00:01:26,939
Good grief.

23
00:01:28,126 --> 00:01:29,926
Look at this.
What are you going to do now?

24
00:01:30,053 --> 00:01:31,699
You wrecked your father's bumper.

25
00:01:31,973 --> 00:01:33,700
The bumper isn't what matters right now.

26
00:01:33,899 --> 00:01:36,412
I thought
something terrible had happened to you.

27
00:01:36,413 --> 00:01:38,066
Haven't you ever seen someone get carsick?

28
00:01:39,606 --> 00:01:41,646
Are you hurt anywhere?

29
00:01:42,499 --> 00:01:43,979
Why would I be hurt?

30
00:01:45,052 --> 00:01:47,186
Getting back in that car
isn't happening, is it?

31
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:49,593
Well...

32
00:01:50,086 --> 00:01:52,006
I'll drive there somehow.

33
00:01:52,279 --> 00:01:54,853
You take the bus. It's not far from here.

34
00:01:55,359 --> 00:01:57,966
Or do you want to walk a bit
until the nausea passes?

35
00:01:58,980 --> 00:02:00,080
Okay, let's do that.

36
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:07,073
Get ready. Your family's probably worried.

37
00:02:30,113 --> 00:02:32,800
What happened
that's giving you such a hard time?

38
00:02:34,399 --> 00:02:35,700
I hate seeing you in pain.

39
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:38,019
Please stop hurting.

40
00:02:58,806 --> 00:02:59,806
Sleep tight.

41
00:03:00,739 --> 00:03:01,993
I'll come pick you up
early tomorrow morning.

42
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,339
Don't go, Min Ho.

43
00:03:14,233 --> 00:03:15,233
Seung Ri.

44
00:03:17,133 --> 00:03:18,666
I don't want to be alone.

45
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,079
Stay with me.

46
00:03:22,846 --> 00:03:23,846
Please.

47
00:03:34,959 --> 00:03:37,538
About last night...

48
00:03:37,539 --> 00:03:38,539
Min Ho.

49
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,620
It was my choice.

50
00:03:44,039 --> 00:03:45,346
Don't read too much into it.

51
00:03:45,986 --> 00:03:46,986
Seung Ri.

52
00:03:48,259 --> 00:03:49,826
Why would you say something like that?

53
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:52,039
I never took it lightly.

54
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:54,579
I know how you felt.

55
00:03:59,359 --> 00:04:02,092
I was having a hard time.

56
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:05,200
So...

57
00:04:08,026 --> 00:04:09,166
I leaned on you for a while.

58
00:04:13,059 --> 00:04:14,059
Min Ho.

59
00:04:20,919 --> 00:04:22,259
The moment I walk out of here,

60
00:04:22,940 --> 00:04:24,266
I'll forget everything.

61
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:29,173
You should do the same.

62
00:04:29,593 --> 00:04:30,593
Seo Seung Ri.

63
00:04:31,966 --> 00:04:34,993
What on earth happened
that's giving you such a hard time?

64
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:38,346
You can just tell me everything.

65
00:04:39,733 --> 00:04:41,339
We're about to start the second round.

66
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,300
Let's get back to work.

67
00:04:56,793 --> 00:04:57,793
Wait!

68
00:04:57,793 --> 00:05:00,351
And who are you? His girlfriend?

69
00:05:00,352 --> 00:05:02,700
Yeah!
So what are you going to do about it?

70
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:07,400
She said she's my girlfriend.
My girlfriend.

71
00:05:08,739 --> 00:05:10,606
Did she mean it?

72
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:13,539
Or was it just something...

73
00:05:13,679 --> 00:05:14,799
she said to get us out of trouble?

74
00:05:16,886 --> 00:05:20,013
For something off the cuff,
she sure sounded sincere.

75
00:05:20,373 --> 00:05:22,486
She was sincere about saving me.

76
00:05:23,053 --> 00:05:24,053
Seriously.

77
00:05:24,912 --> 00:05:25,979
Hey, Seo Seung Ri!

78
00:05:29,719 --> 00:05:31,452
What's gotten into you?

79
00:05:31,913 --> 00:05:33,679
Your phone's been off since yesterday.

80
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:35,399
Where have you been?

81
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,632
I'm sorry, Mom. Were you worried?

82
00:05:37,633 --> 00:05:38,633
Just worried?

83
00:05:39,326 --> 00:05:42,792
Min Ho kept saying he couldn't reach you.

84
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:44,893
A friend came by the office,

85
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:46,486
and I guess I drank too much
during the day.

86
00:05:46,806 --> 00:05:48,632
I went to my friend's place
and fell asleep.

87
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:49,633
What?

88
00:05:50,192 --> 00:05:51,792
How much did you drink?

89
00:05:52,466 --> 00:05:54,946
Seung Ri, what happened?

90
00:05:56,026 --> 00:05:59,199
I'm sorry.
I'm exhausted, so I'm going to my room.

91
00:06:00,839 --> 00:06:02,339
- Seriously...
- Just leave her alone.

92
00:06:04,139 --> 00:06:05,619
I'm sure she has her reasons.

93
00:06:06,473 --> 00:06:07,700
Seung Ri's over 30 now.

94
00:06:07,773 --> 00:06:09,253
Would our Seung Ri really get so drunk...

95
00:06:09,413 --> 00:06:11,119
that she'd spend the night out
without even calling?

96
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:13,213
No way!

97
00:06:13,499 --> 00:06:14,526
Seo Seung Ri spent the night out?

98
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:16,353
This is huge!

99
00:06:17,406 --> 00:06:18,406
With Min Ho?

100
00:06:18,953 --> 00:06:19,953
Seriously.

101
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,319
- Watch your mouth!
- Mom, wait!

102
00:06:24,173 --> 00:06:26,139
Why do your hands hurt so much?

103
00:06:26,686 --> 00:06:28,499
They're getting worse every day.

104
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:31,192
Anyway...

105
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:34,220
Mom, you packed me lunch before.

106
00:06:34,379 --> 00:06:35,546
Could you make me one again?

107
00:06:36,586 --> 00:06:37,700
I don't know why...

108
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:39,700
Maybe it's because it's the season
when everyone gets hungry, but...

109
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,332
I'm starving all the time.

110
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,026
What season?

111
00:06:43,359 --> 00:06:44,700
It's the middle of summer.

112
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:45,886
You are talking nonsense...

113
00:06:45,886 --> 00:06:46,952
- What are you...
- Seriously!

114
00:06:47,573 --> 00:06:49,333
Who says...

115
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:51,300
only autumn makes people hungry?

116
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,366
Anyway, like last time,

117
00:06:53,479 --> 00:06:55,059
make lots of different dishes.
Plenty of them.

118
00:06:55,279 --> 00:06:56,659
And make them really good.

119
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,006
Thank you!

120
00:07:00,559 --> 00:07:02,006
Mrs. Kang.

121
00:07:02,006 --> 00:07:03,866
What a surprise.

122
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:07,646
Don't tell me you've found
a nice blind date for Min Ho.

123
00:07:09,319 --> 00:07:11,852
What? What did you just say?

124
00:07:12,426 --> 00:07:13,546
Min Ho was at a hotel...

125
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:16,133
with a woman?

126
00:07:18,879 --> 00:07:20,579
That can't be right.

127
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:22,053
You must've been mistaken.

128
00:07:22,053 --> 00:07:23,819
He doesn't even have a girlfriend.

129
00:07:25,073 --> 00:07:26,073
I'm home.

130
00:07:26,073 --> 00:07:28,453
Mrs. Kang, I'll call you back later.

131
00:07:30,699 --> 00:07:31,953
Where are you coming from?

132
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:34,220
I'm tired. I'm going upstairs.

133
00:07:46,079 --> 00:07:47,466
Who was the woman?

134
00:07:48,633 --> 00:07:49,633
What woman?

135
00:07:49,646 --> 00:07:51,106
Two hours ago, you were at a hotel...

136
00:07:52,646 --> 00:07:53,846
Back in the old days,

137
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:57,873
a grown son like you
would've had three or four kids by now.

138
00:07:57,873 --> 00:08:00,173
So maybe I shouldn't be asking this...

139
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:02,553
Stop beating around the bush.

140
00:08:02,973 --> 00:08:04,119
Who did you sleep with last night?

141
00:08:04,693 --> 00:08:07,666
Someone saw you leaving a hotel
with a woman this morning.

142
00:08:08,066 --> 00:08:09,739
Don't try to dodge the question.

143
00:08:10,346 --> 00:08:11,346
Who was she?

144
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:13,225
Seriously? Who was it?

145
00:08:13,226 --> 00:08:14,586
Who was that woman?

146
00:08:14,772 --> 00:08:16,739
It wasn't Seung Ri, was it?

147
00:08:17,346 --> 00:08:18,658
No. It can't be.

148
00:08:18,659 --> 00:08:19,659
It'd better not be.

149
00:08:19,659 --> 00:08:20,786
Mom, Dad.

150
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,040
Could you please leave?

151
00:08:23,799 --> 00:08:25,679
How dare you tell your parents to leave?

152
00:08:26,146 --> 00:08:27,232
Just answer the question!

153
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:28,412
Please!

154
00:08:29,319 --> 00:08:30,891
Just leave, okay?

155
00:08:30,892 --> 00:08:32,426
Fine! We'll go!

156
00:08:32,846 --> 00:08:35,252
- Let's go. Retreat.
- Why?

157
00:08:35,253 --> 00:08:37,566
Hey, Ko Min Ho. It wasn't Seung Ri, right?

158
00:08:37,953 --> 00:08:40,246
It can't be. It'd better not be.

159
00:08:40,606 --> 00:08:41,706
You'll be in big trouble.

160
00:08:44,186 --> 00:08:47,252
He doesn't look like a guy
who just spent the night with a woman.

161
00:08:47,253 --> 00:08:49,100
Looks more like he got punched
in the face.

162
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:52,006
He's doing that on purpose to shut us up.

163
00:08:52,693 --> 00:08:54,026
Is that what it is?

164
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:55,546
I'm calling that woman right now.

165
00:08:55,726 --> 00:08:57,233
Hold on.

166
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,500
Who are you calling?

167
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:01,426
I'm calling Seung Ri's mom.

168
00:09:01,426 --> 00:09:03,566
I need to find out
if Seung Ri spent the night out too.

169
00:09:04,766 --> 00:09:06,798
Crystal, don't stir up trouble.

170
00:09:06,799 --> 00:09:07,926
Just sit tight.

171
00:09:07,926 --> 00:09:09,266
Take a deep breath.

172
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:18,573
Besides, our son's already in his mid-30s.

173
00:09:19,019 --> 00:09:20,500
What's the big deal
if he spent the night out?

174
00:09:21,619 --> 00:09:24,386
Don't you know what matters most
right now?

175
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:25,520
Right.

176
00:09:26,173 --> 00:09:27,632
I almost forgot.

177
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:30,006
You've got everything planned, don't you?

178
00:09:30,260 --> 00:09:31,400
Of course.

179
00:09:32,026 --> 00:09:33,525
The moment I get to the office tomorrow,

180
00:09:33,526 --> 00:09:36,086
I'm settling this
with that punk Seong Jun.

181
00:09:36,446 --> 00:09:39,259
Good. I'll handle Kang Yeon Ja.

182
00:09:40,326 --> 00:09:42,032
How dare she think
she can be my sister-in-law?

183
00:09:42,466 --> 00:09:43,719
Not a chance.

184
00:09:50,473 --> 00:09:51,759
Give it to me. I'll clean it up.

185
00:09:53,026 --> 00:09:55,472
The sink drain was completely clogged
with hardened grease.

186
00:09:55,839 --> 00:09:57,365
I cleared it with my tools,

187
00:09:57,366 --> 00:09:58,733
so it should be fine for quite a while.

188
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:00,879
Don't pour grease down the drain anymore,
okay?

189
00:10:01,759 --> 00:10:05,138
And I sealed the bathroom leak
with waterproof silicone,

190
00:10:05,139 --> 00:10:06,539
so don't use the water until tomorrow.

191
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:08,979
Thank you for all your hard work.

192
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:10,386
Come on over and sit down.

193
00:10:11,326 --> 00:10:12,326
Okay.

194
00:10:12,513 --> 00:10:14,132
Are you really feeling all right?

195
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:17,339
Can't you tell by how lively I am?

196
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:25,500
Goodness, look at all that sweat.

197
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:27,446
Here, drink this.

198
00:10:27,599 --> 00:10:29,353
It's a roasted multigrain shake
with plenty of ice.

199
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:31,173
You should have a cup too, dear.

200
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,860
Thank you.

201
00:10:37,193 --> 00:10:38,673
This is so nutty and refreshing.

202
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:41,986
The young man is drenched in sweat.

203
00:10:42,386 --> 00:10:45,612
You should give him a nice scrubdown.

204
00:10:45,613 --> 00:10:46,920
What? A scrubdown?

205
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:50,993
I don't think I can do that.

206
00:10:52,606 --> 00:10:54,573
If you like it, just admit it.

207
00:10:55,153 --> 00:10:58,740
Last time, you two insisted
you were nothing to each other.

208
00:10:58,740 --> 00:11:00,520
- Exactly.
- Goodness.

209
00:11:00,780 --> 00:11:02,393
That's what youth is all about.

210
00:11:04,213 --> 00:11:06,033
You fight, then fall in love.

211
00:11:06,033 --> 00:11:07,633
Your boyfriend becomes your husband.

212
00:11:08,613 --> 00:11:10,873
Where did all my youth go?

213
00:11:12,386 --> 00:11:16,059
It feels like I blinked and it was gone.

214
00:11:16,733 --> 00:11:19,526
What are you talking about?
You're still in your prime.

215
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,093
We should get going. We have work to do.

216
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:24,680
We'll come visit again.

217
00:11:25,206 --> 00:11:26,513
What are you talking about?

218
00:11:26,513 --> 00:11:27,846
A card shark came all this way.

219
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:30,246
We have to play a round of Go-Stop.

220
00:11:30,247 --> 00:11:31,385
- Right.
- Absolutely.

221
00:11:31,386 --> 00:11:33,205
Grandma,
we have a very important presentation...

222
00:11:33,206 --> 00:11:36,218
at work the day after tomorrow. I'm sorry.

223
00:11:36,219 --> 00:11:38,046
Please let us off just this once.

224
00:11:39,046 --> 00:11:40,812
How can you leave
after coming all this way?

225
00:11:40,813 --> 00:11:42,406
- Exactly.
- If you leave now...

226
00:11:44,373 --> 00:11:45,865
Goodness gracious.

227
00:11:45,873 --> 00:11:48,313
This is why blood ties are so powerful.

228
00:11:48,613 --> 00:11:51,513
All this time,
your blood was drawing you together.

229
00:11:51,906 --> 00:11:55,791
Meeting again and again.

230
00:11:55,792 --> 00:11:57,491
Sun Bun, what have you been listening to?

231
00:11:57,492 --> 00:11:58,699
Blood ties?

232
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:01,091
I'm never seeing that woman again.

233
00:12:01,092 --> 00:12:03,919
Even so, you shouldn't
call your own mom "that woman."

234
00:12:04,453 --> 00:12:07,845
You said she had no choice.

235
00:12:07,846 --> 00:12:11,286
So the child who was abandoned
has to understand why she was abandoned?

236
00:12:12,113 --> 00:12:13,992
You're the only one
who understands how I feel,

237
00:12:13,999 --> 00:12:15,286
so I came here just to vent a little.

238
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:17,333
What? Wait.

239
00:12:18,032 --> 00:12:19,032
Hey...

240
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,000
What's wrong, Grandma?

241
00:12:25,166 --> 00:12:26,233
Did you two have an argument?

242
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:28,906
No, we didn't.

243
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:32,760
Then what is it? Tell me.

244
00:12:33,026 --> 00:12:34,026
Well...

245
00:12:34,866 --> 00:12:36,026
You see...

246
00:12:37,979 --> 00:12:39,839
My goodness. How?

247
00:12:40,740 --> 00:12:42,600
What happens now?

248
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,833
She may be like that now,

249
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:47,933
but one day,
I'm sure they'll embrace each other again.

250
00:12:48,606 --> 00:12:51,046
No, that's not what I meant.
I mean Eun Ae.

251
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:53,186
She and Team Manager Ko are...

252
00:12:53,753 --> 00:12:56,426
But if they share the same grandmother...

253
00:12:56,526 --> 00:12:59,192
That's another complication.

254
00:13:00,879 --> 00:13:02,793
What are we going to do about Eun Ae?

255
00:13:02,959 --> 00:13:04,492
She finally found her spring.

256
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,973
Is that what matters right now?

257
00:13:07,153 --> 00:13:11,179
A mother and daughter have reunited
after 50 years!

258
00:13:14,726 --> 00:13:17,253
Mother, why did you make so much food?

259
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:21,792
Leave this in the pantry
and put it in the fridge tomorrow morning.

260
00:13:21,793 --> 00:13:22,793
Yes, Madam.

261
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:27,019
Mother, don't tell me...

262
00:13:27,019 --> 00:13:29,326
you made all this
to take to Kang Yeon Ja's house.

263
00:13:30,559 --> 00:13:33,399
It seems like she's trying
to cut ties with you,

264
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:35,666
so why are you bringing her food?

265
00:13:36,126 --> 00:13:38,699
Su Jeong, listen to me carefully.

266
00:13:39,933 --> 00:13:43,533
I may not be Dae Chi's birth mother,

267
00:13:44,306 --> 00:13:46,073
but I raised him with my own hands
for 50 years.

268
00:13:46,506 --> 00:13:47,553
Sorry?

269
00:13:48,119 --> 00:13:50,066
Why are you saying that all of a sudden?

270
00:13:50,633 --> 00:13:52,986
Just as Dae Chi
is no different from my own son,

271
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:57,720
my daughter is the Chairman's child,
no matter what anyone says.

272
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:00,639
So if you're thinking
of getting in the way,

273
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:02,200
give it up now.

274
00:14:02,599 --> 00:14:05,406
Mother, are you saying...

275
00:14:06,326 --> 00:14:09,599
you want to add Kang Yeon Ja
to Father's family registry?

276
00:14:09,599 --> 00:14:10,818
Is that what you're saying?

277
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,200
What?

278
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:16,139
Kang Yeon Ja isn't related
to Father by blood at all.

279
00:14:16,140 --> 00:14:17,366
What are you talking about?

280
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:19,233
Not related?

281
00:14:20,093 --> 00:14:21,093
Father.

282
00:14:22,613 --> 00:14:23,946
If you're not here to help, then leave.

283
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:26,160
Yes, Father.

284
00:14:29,653 --> 00:14:31,986
I made too much for something...

285
00:14:32,753 --> 00:14:34,686
I can't even take to Yeon Sun.

286
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:37,566
Why can't you? Just take it to her.

287
00:14:38,193 --> 00:14:40,179
She won't want anything I cooked.

288
00:14:41,472 --> 00:14:44,079
All I ever made was soybean paste soup
with dried radish greens and radish salad.

289
00:14:45,233 --> 00:14:46,233
On her birthdays,

290
00:14:47,146 --> 00:14:49,959
all she got was seaweed soup
with perilla powder...

291
00:14:50,612 --> 00:14:52,426
and some green onion pancakes.

292
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:55,973
I couldn't feed her well
when she was little,

293
00:14:56,500 --> 00:15:00,306
so I wanted to make things for her now.

294
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:04,673
But I just don't have the courage
to bring it to her.

295
00:15:05,906 --> 00:15:07,786
If you can't bring it to her,

296
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:12,226
then I will. So don't think like that.

297
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,320
Do everything you've wanted to do for her.

298
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:28,660
What's that smell?

299
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,733
It smells like soybean paste soup
with dried radish greens.

300
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,433
What? Yeah.

301
00:15:33,180 --> 00:15:36,126
I hadn't shopped in days,
so there wasn't much to make.

302
00:15:36,373 --> 00:15:39,639
I suddenly wanted soybean paste soup
with dried radish greens and radish salad.

303
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:43,340
What should we do?
Dinner's all vegetables tonight.

304
00:15:43,546 --> 00:15:46,066
What are you talking about?

305
00:15:46,373 --> 00:15:49,099
Those are my favorite side dishes
you make.

306
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:52,072
Honey...

307
00:15:53,553 --> 00:15:55,786
Could you quit Kangsu Construction?

308
00:15:56,979 --> 00:15:57,979
What?

309
00:15:58,193 --> 00:15:59,993
I'm really sorry to say this,

310
00:16:00,479 --> 00:16:03,426
but I wish both you and Eun Ae
would leave that company.

311
00:16:03,899 --> 00:16:04,899
Honey.

312
00:16:05,126 --> 00:16:07,006
I know it sounds unreasonable.

313
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:10,820
I know how hard things were
when you were unemployed.

314
00:16:11,753 --> 00:16:15,506
But as long as you and Eun Ae
keep working there,

315
00:16:15,973 --> 00:16:17,846
we'll never be free from all this.

316
00:16:19,713 --> 00:16:21,826
I understand what you're saying,

317
00:16:22,339 --> 00:16:24,439
but to us, it's just our workplace.

318
00:16:24,859 --> 00:16:25,992
Especially for Eun Ae...

319
00:16:26,460 --> 00:16:27,460
All right.

320
00:16:28,406 --> 00:16:29,840
I shouldn't have said anything.

321
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:32,132
Go call Eun Hyeong and Bit Na downstairs.

322
00:16:32,133 --> 00:16:33,133
I'll get dinner ready.

323
00:16:49,699 --> 00:16:51,173
It doesn't taste like it used to.

324
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,059
I just uploaded the presentation file
to the group chat.

325
00:16:56,266 --> 00:16:59,033
Okay. I uploaded the final version
of the second design too.

326
00:17:01,506 --> 00:17:02,639
Should we call it a day?

327
00:17:02,793 --> 00:17:04,819
Yes, I'm exhausted.

328
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,673
Every part of my body aches.

329
00:17:06,813 --> 00:17:09,619
That's because you were gripping the wheel
so hard with that rusty driving.

330
00:17:10,246 --> 00:17:12,379
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have made you drive.

331
00:17:12,999 --> 00:17:15,306
Team Manager, are you really okay?

332
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:16,519
Come on.

333
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:19,279
Why do you keep asking me that today?

334
00:17:19,686 --> 00:17:21,412
Have you never seen anyone get carsick?

335
00:17:21,546 --> 00:17:24,098
I don't think it was just carsickness.

336
00:17:24,099 --> 00:17:25,666
If it wasn't just carsickness,
then what was it?

337
00:17:26,753 --> 00:17:28,859
Let's go home.

338
00:17:30,326 --> 00:17:31,892
We're taking the elevator today.

339
00:17:31,893 --> 00:17:32,893
I'm really tired.

340
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,718
No thanks.

341
00:17:34,719 --> 00:17:37,199
I never have time to work out,
so I'm taking the stairs.

342
00:17:37,346 --> 00:17:38,346
See you in the lobby.

343
00:17:38,346 --> 00:17:41,413
Just take the elevator down.

344
00:17:43,033 --> 00:17:45,693
Team Manager,
about the accident earlier...

345
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:47,573
You never take the elevator either.

346
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:51,732
Do you have claustrophobia?

347
00:17:51,733 --> 00:17:53,185
Or maybe panic...

348
00:17:53,186 --> 00:17:55,132
Airport? Where'd that come from?

349
00:17:55,513 --> 00:17:57,479
Do you suddenly want to fly somewhere?

350
00:17:57,679 --> 00:17:59,586
I wish I had the time to travel.

351
00:18:01,146 --> 00:18:02,152
But are you really okay?

352
00:18:02,152 --> 00:18:05,486
- What are you talking about?
- I'm worried.

353
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:22,233
No.

354
00:18:23,479 --> 00:18:24,479
No!

355
00:18:27,153 --> 00:18:28,153
What's wrong, little bro?

356
00:18:28,593 --> 00:18:29,626
What's wrong?

357
00:18:33,313 --> 00:18:35,499
What's wrong? Did you have a nightmare?

358
00:18:36,473 --> 00:18:37,473
No.

359
00:18:37,966 --> 00:18:39,879
I just had a bout of sleep paralysis.

360
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:43,746
I guess sleeping on the floor
is uncomfortable for you.

361
00:18:44,366 --> 00:18:45,846
Come sleep on the bed.
I'll sleep on the floor.

362
00:18:46,453 --> 00:18:47,893
No. That's not it.

363
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,879
I'll just go get some fresh air.

364
00:18:51,286 --> 00:18:52,353
Good night.

365
00:18:56,213 --> 00:18:57,213
Wait...

366
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,500
I need to find a place and move out soon.

367
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:09,613
Father, you're still awake?

368
00:19:10,272 --> 00:19:12,639
Yeah. Why are you out here,
Team Manager Ko?

369
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:14,906
I just came out for some fresh air.

370
00:19:15,533 --> 00:19:18,566
By the way, they said replacing the bumper
will take about two days.

371
00:19:18,766 --> 00:19:20,412
I'm sorry. It was my fault...

372
00:19:20,413 --> 00:19:22,086
for asking Eun Ae to borrow a car.

373
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:25,040
As long as neither of you got hurt,
that's all that matters.

374
00:19:25,126 --> 00:19:27,873
Okay. Your wife's still having
a hard time, isn't she?

375
00:19:29,173 --> 00:19:30,173
She is.

376
00:19:32,266 --> 00:19:33,266
Team Manager Ko.

377
00:19:33,626 --> 00:19:36,453
I don't know how to say this, but...

378
00:19:37,819 --> 00:19:38,999
You and Eun Ae...

379
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,659
You know you're cousins, right?

380
00:19:42,233 --> 00:19:45,386
Right.
I know exactly what you're worried about.

381
00:19:45,759 --> 00:19:49,019
But, there's no problem between us.

382
00:19:51,446 --> 00:19:54,313
The truth is, I'm adopted.

383
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:59,406
When I was seven, the Chairman
adopted me as CEO Ko Dae Chi's son.

384
00:20:00,153 --> 00:20:02,886
What? Wait...

385
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:07,786
Then you're not CEO Ko's biological son?

386
00:20:08,599 --> 00:20:09,599
No, Father.

387
00:20:10,152 --> 00:20:11,726
If it's only about blood ties,

388
00:20:12,359 --> 00:20:14,306
there's really no problem between us.

389
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:41,460
Dad, do you have a minute?

390
00:20:41,853 --> 00:20:44,672
Sure. What's up?

391
00:20:45,066 --> 00:20:48,799
About 25 years ago, you worked
at the Eastern European branch, right?

392
00:20:49,886 --> 00:20:51,086
Why bring that up all of a sudden?

393
00:20:51,812 --> 00:20:53,846
I was just looking through
our old photo albums,

394
00:20:54,566 --> 00:20:56,766
and I couldn't find
a single picture of you from that time.

395
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:58,193
Seung Ri...

396
00:20:58,333 --> 00:20:59,466
Mom told me...

397
00:21:00,473 --> 00:21:01,566
that after you went bankrupt,

398
00:21:02,086 --> 00:21:05,393
the Chairman took our whole family in.

399
00:21:06,213 --> 00:21:08,240
So you devoted yourself to work...

400
00:21:08,919 --> 00:21:11,412
and couldn't come home
even once for five years.

401
00:21:13,060 --> 00:21:15,086
Even so...

402
00:21:15,626 --> 00:21:17,032
When I entered elementary school,

403
00:21:17,033 --> 00:21:19,533
you didn't even call to congratulate me.

404
00:21:20,733 --> 00:21:23,686
The Dad I know now
never would've done that.

405
00:21:24,273 --> 00:21:26,373
I guess I really let you down.

406
00:21:27,233 --> 00:21:28,233
I'm sorry.

407
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:29,700
Don't apologize.

408
00:21:31,106 --> 00:21:34,333
That'll make it seem like
you really did something wrong.

409
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,000
Seung Ri.

410
00:21:36,746 --> 00:21:38,752
I'm just a little hurt.

411
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:40,900
Good night.

412
00:21:56,393 --> 00:21:58,839
(Kangsu Construction)

413
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:00,626
What are you talking about?

414
00:22:01,566 --> 00:22:02,999
We approached you on purpose?

415
00:22:03,546 --> 00:22:04,626
Come on.

416
00:22:04,626 --> 00:22:06,966
You got a job as a janitor
at Kangsu Construction,

417
00:22:07,393 --> 00:22:09,726
your daughter became an intern
in the planning division,

418
00:22:10,993 --> 00:22:14,546
and your wife joined
our company's line dancing class.

419
00:22:14,546 --> 00:22:16,086
You expect me to believe
all that's just a coincidence?

420
00:22:16,413 --> 00:22:19,573
So you're saying our whole family
knew who the Chairman's wife was...

421
00:22:20,473 --> 00:22:21,940
and deliberately got close to your family?

422
00:22:22,433 --> 00:22:24,146
Exactly. That's exactly what I'm saying.

423
00:22:24,666 --> 00:22:27,033
From my point of view,

424
00:22:27,033 --> 00:22:28,972
I can't help but be suspicious.

425
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,600
Mr. Cho.

426
00:22:31,119 --> 00:22:33,199
I'm warning you.
Don't even think about it.

427
00:22:33,667 --> 00:22:35,866
Getting onto
my father's family registry...

428
00:22:35,866 --> 00:22:37,713
and getting your hands
on Kangsu Group's shares...

429
00:22:37,713 --> 00:22:38,713
Sir!

430
00:22:39,646 --> 00:22:40,646
Good grief.

431
00:22:40,979 --> 00:22:42,919
Did you just raise your voice at me?

432
00:22:43,340 --> 00:22:45,293
This is insubordination!

433
00:22:46,153 --> 00:22:48,185
Even if we ended up becoming...

434
00:22:48,186 --> 00:22:51,213
brothers-in-law, this is...

435
00:22:52,153 --> 00:22:53,153
Brothers-in-law?

436
00:22:54,766 --> 00:22:56,166
Don't flatter yourself.

437
00:22:56,560 --> 00:22:57,833
Neither my wife nor I...

438
00:22:58,160 --> 00:23:01,966
have the slightest interest
in your family's registry or shares.

439
00:23:02,953 --> 00:23:04,433
That's enough.

440
00:23:06,246 --> 00:23:07,346
Listen.

441
00:23:07,346 --> 00:23:10,438
You just swore with your own mouth...

442
00:23:10,439 --> 00:23:13,112
that you have no interest...

443
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:15,679
in the family registry
or Kangsu Group's shares.

444
00:23:16,079 --> 00:23:17,746
Don't change your story later.

445
00:23:19,266 --> 00:23:20,966
The second round
is the day after tomorrow.

446
00:23:21,572 --> 00:23:23,533
Please focus on your work.

447
00:23:23,886 --> 00:23:25,153
Fine. Now I can finally focus.

448
00:23:25,153 --> 00:23:26,933
All right. You may go.

449
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:31,040
Right.

450
00:23:32,433 --> 00:23:34,646
I heard Team Manager Ko is adopted.

451
00:23:35,739 --> 00:23:38,392
Who told you that?

452
00:23:38,713 --> 00:23:41,386
Is that why you've been so biased
toward Team One in this competition?

453
00:23:43,066 --> 00:23:45,286
If you really want to become
the true owner of Kangsu Group,

454
00:23:45,533 --> 00:23:47,533
then start acting like one.

455
00:23:54,686 --> 00:23:55,686
What's with that punk?

456
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,553
How much does he actually know?

457
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,000
You punk!

458
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:07,813
How dare you come in here?

459
00:24:10,613 --> 00:24:11,613
Sir.

460
00:24:11,933 --> 00:24:15,626
I think I've found the solution
for Team One to win.

461
00:24:17,346 --> 00:24:18,346
A solution?

462
00:24:20,386 --> 00:24:23,066
Mr. Han Ji Hun,
pull up the sports robot simulation.

463
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:25,546
Yes. Here it is.

464
00:24:27,433 --> 00:24:29,386
When do you expect mass production
to begin?

465
00:24:29,853 --> 00:24:32,019
Well,
we don't have a concrete schedule yet.

466
00:24:32,260 --> 00:24:34,713
If the judges ask you that
during the presentation,

467
00:24:34,933 --> 00:24:36,392
are you going to answer like that?

468
00:24:38,260 --> 00:24:41,859
Contact the robot manufacturer
and get an exact production schedule.

469
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:44,053
Yes, ma'am.

470
00:24:44,426 --> 00:24:47,719
I heard Ms. Cho Eun Ae
will be presenting for Team Two.

471
00:24:48,166 --> 00:24:50,105
Joy's integration
is one of the main evaluation criteria,

472
00:24:50,106 --> 00:24:52,013
so I guess they're having
the developer present it herself.

473
00:24:52,292 --> 00:24:53,312
That makes sense.

474
00:24:53,926 --> 00:24:55,432
In that case...

475
00:24:56,866 --> 00:24:58,626
- Can you do it?
- Yes, absolutely.

476
00:24:59,419 --> 00:25:01,626
If you give me the chance,
I'll do my very best.

477
00:25:02,872 --> 00:25:04,899
Good. Then our team...

478
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:07,179
will have the Joy developer
give the presentation too.

479
00:25:07,792 --> 00:25:08,792
Shall we take a short break?

480
00:25:09,039 --> 00:25:11,839
Sure. We'll go grab some cold drinks.

481
00:25:17,973 --> 00:25:20,686
Are you sure it's okay
to make him the presenter?

482
00:25:21,733 --> 00:25:24,372
He knows Joy better than I do.

483
00:25:25,253 --> 00:25:26,653
Why? What's bothering you now?

484
00:25:27,673 --> 00:25:30,140
Nothing.
If that's your decision, I'll follow it.

485
00:25:32,926 --> 00:25:33,926
Are you okay?

486
00:25:34,526 --> 00:25:35,526
About what?

487
00:25:36,406 --> 00:25:38,306
We need to talk.

488
00:25:39,119 --> 00:25:40,119
When are you free?

489
00:25:41,766 --> 00:25:44,566
If you have something to say,
I'm free right now.

490
00:25:46,233 --> 00:25:49,319
Okay.
Let's focus on the competition first.

491
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:51,000
We'll talk later.

492
00:25:55,292 --> 00:25:57,053
Great work, everyone.

493
00:25:57,186 --> 00:25:59,600
The last train leaves soon,
so I'm heading out first.

494
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:00,600
- Okay.
- See you tomorrow.

495
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:01,886
- Goodbye, Assistant Manager.
- Bye.

496
00:26:04,533 --> 00:26:06,412
You're not going to suggest...

497
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:09,332
another online rehearsal tonight, are you?

498
00:26:09,333 --> 00:26:10,333
Come on.

499
00:26:10,333 --> 00:26:12,399
We can rehearse face-to-face at home.
Why would we do it online?

500
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,899
Someone might get the wrong idea.

501
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:17,526
Who's going to hear us?

502
00:26:17,753 --> 00:26:19,319
Team One already left too.

503
00:26:20,733 --> 00:26:23,199
Are you taking
the emergency stairs again today?

504
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:24,946
Yes. That's the plan.

505
00:26:34,546 --> 00:26:36,046
- Why won't this open?
- Let me try.

506
00:26:38,299 --> 00:26:39,766
That's strange.

507
00:26:40,413 --> 00:26:41,780
Why is the emergency exit locked?

508
00:26:44,046 --> 00:26:45,046
We've got no choice.

509
00:26:45,432 --> 00:26:47,919
Let's just take the elevator.
We might as well.

510
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:48,920
Yes!

511
00:26:59,792 --> 00:27:01,099
What? What's going on?

512
00:27:02,813 --> 00:27:05,053
Is it broken? Hang on.

513
00:27:07,846 --> 00:27:10,486
That's weird.
Why isn't the emergency button working?

514
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:17,040
What's wrong, Team Manager?

515
00:27:17,300 --> 00:27:18,706
Is it happening again, like last time?

516
00:27:19,612 --> 00:27:20,612
What do we do?

517
00:27:25,706 --> 00:27:26,839
Are you okay, Team Manager?

518
00:27:27,933 --> 00:27:29,292
Just hang in there, okay?

519
00:27:29,526 --> 00:27:30,526
Someone...

520
00:27:30,866 --> 00:27:31,886
The security camera!

521
00:27:32,699 --> 00:27:35,992
Help! Someone's trapped in here!

522
00:27:35,992 --> 00:27:38,899
Help! Someone's trapped in here!

523
00:27:38,900 --> 00:27:39,900
Help!

524
00:27:47,013 --> 00:27:48,013
Hang on!

525
00:27:49,900 --> 00:27:51,033
Just stay still.

526
00:27:52,813 --> 00:27:53,813
Please!

527
00:28:03,233 --> 00:28:05,833
(Our Happy Days)

528
00:28:06,100 --> 00:28:08,059
Why record it? Now I'm nervous.

529
00:28:08,146 --> 00:28:10,333
Look at me. Pretend I'm one of the judges.

530
00:28:10,534 --> 00:28:11,666
Look me in the eye.

531
00:28:11,666 --> 00:28:14,838
Talk some sense into him.

532
00:28:14,839 --> 00:28:16,667
Team Manager Ko is adopted.

533
00:28:16,667 --> 00:28:17,667
What?

534
00:28:17,667 --> 00:28:19,799
I'm Cho Eun Ae,
